## Final Acceptance Criteria

The work is done when all of the following are true:

1. Running `ncd <query>` with no service behaves as before.
2. Running `ncd <query>` with service active avoids reloading metadata/database from disk and instead uses mapped shared state.
3. Matching, UI behavior, and agent mode output remain client-side and match standalone mode.
4. Heuristic and metadata updates flow back to the service and persist correctly.
5. Service publication is safe, versioned, validated, and pointer-free.
6. Both Linux and Windows implementations work with the same high-level design.
7. Tests and timing data prove correctness and value.

